•	Firstly we need to install OpenCV
•	Ok so basically since I’m working with AprilTag, I copied a premade git repo into my system, and now I’m on 36h11 which looks somewhat like this, with each tag having a different pattern. 
•	Tag36h11 means 36 bit code, with hamming distance of 11. Bit code is basically the binary code, and hamming code is the dissimilarity between 2 data. Uses xor gate to compare. There are so many tags being used as trackers, which are used to note different objects. Used mostly for identification purposes. Also do not worry about the red of the image, its not an error, just a git thing.
