Detect tags , Show result , Repeat , Repeat , Repeat , Repeat... First it checks if the frame is showing a proper picture, and returns true, if not then false.
•	Then the image is converted to grayscale using gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY) 
•	Now, all the tags are detected, and stored in the form of a list. Prints all the different tag ids. 
•	Then it gets the coordinates of all the corners of each tag
•	We now draw on the webcam frame, and take the x and y coordinates for each corner. We draw green lines connecting each adjacent corner, and creating a box. Then, create a circle of radius 5 for each corner, with the colour red. So, make red dots on each of the corners of each of the tags. 
•	Now, we calculate the pixel width for the tags, and calculate the scale. Also, we make dots at the centre of each side.
•	Then, we write information of the tag. We write the tag id, display width, scale.
